LAFIA – The Nigeria Labour Congress (NLC) from the North-Central zone on Wednesday staged a protest to the Nasarawa State House Assembly to demand for autonomy for local government area, Judiciary and Legislature. Speaking while addressing the protesters, the Speaker, Nasarawa State House of Assembly, Ibrahim Abdullahi Balarabe, said the issue of local government autonomy is long overdue and this is the right time to have it done. He explained that for Nasarawa State House Assembly, Labour should go and sleep as well as consider their demands. The Speaker also said that the issue of Judiciary and legislative autonomy has been concluded, waiting for implementation. According to the Speaker, “Mr. President has accented to legislative and Judiciary autonomy and nobody can stop it. Your struggles should be for implementation and very soon, they will commence implementation,” he said. He added that for local government autonomy, as soon as they received a signal from the National Assembly, they would ensure its implementation in the state. Earlier, Yusuf Sarki Iya, the NLC Chairman, Nasarawa , who led other NLC Chairmen of the North Central States, said that the peaceful protest was to demand for state legislature and judiciary, autonomy as well as autonomy for local government. Iya said that autonomy would promote transparency, accountability and good governance in the country. POLL He has commended the House for being workers friendly and called for its sustenance. It would be reported that members of NLC carried placards with different inscriptions such as workers demands for autonomy of LG, State Assemblies and Judicial autonomy, we support councils autonomy among others as the workers comprised of members of all NLC affiliate bodies and their leaders from Nasarawa, Kogi, Plateau, Niger, Kwarra states and the FCT.